      sure. but there's more: a chord played one way can sound different than the 'same' chord played a different way, even on the same instrument. And, even more importantly, the same chord played the exact same way on the same instrument can sound drastically different depending on what came before and after

11.6.22  8:57 am   Do you believe there's been multiple universes before this one?

     i consider 'universe' to include all the time workings. so, because of that, other universes wouldn't be described in any 'time' relationship to each other. If one really was "before" or "after" the other, then i'd have to argue that that's the same universe

     Universes form and eventually destroy themselves so there seems to be no reason that the nothing that follows destruction wouldn't turn into something again. 

     i guess the hard question is what happens to time. and, in that case,..... when?
